.TH "vmw_cmdbuf_idle" 9 "vmw_cmdbuf_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmdbuf_idle \- Wait for command buffer manager idle.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_cmdbuf_idle
.BI "(struct vmw_cmdbuf_man *man "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ","
.BI "unsigned long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "man" 12
The command buffer manager.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Sleep interruptible while waiting.
.IP "timeout" 12
Time out after this many ticks.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait until the command buffer manager has processed all command buffers,
or until a timeout occurs. If a timeout occurs, the function will return
-EBUSY.
